      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Should return an instance of AuthOpt\nJoe\u0027s philosophy is to return the actual struct pointer from constructors like this.  This allows unit tests to more easily poke at the underlying data.  There\u0027s a few other benefits that slip my mind at the moment, but something involving not limiting to interfaces.\n\nTo me, the Init* makes more sense because I am initializing the passed in directory with the given credentials structure.",
