      "message": "Nit: Early on I have used C-style constants as well, but it means exporting them as part of the package. That means when you look at a package/file you cannot tell whether a constant is used outside a package and therefore must be changed with care. \nBy using lower case constants you are guaranteed that the constant is only used within this package. \nSee https://stackoverflow.com/questions/22688906/go-naming-conventions-for-const\nfor a discussion.",
